        <mxCell id="W2oNZioOZXqkSplyH7-h-32" parent="1" style="rounded=1;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;verticalAlign=top;align=left;spacingLeft=8;fontStyle=1;fontSize=13;fillColor=#fff2cc;strokeColor=#d6b656;" value="Workflow Notes" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="200" width="1280" x="120" y="500" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="W2oNZioOZXqkSplyH7-h-33" parent="1" style="text;html=1;align=left;verticalAlign=top;fontSize=12;spacingLeft=10;spacingTop=6;" value="1. Start prompt-service FIRST (port 8000), then prompt-review-service (port 8001) — review service depends on prompt-service being reachable.&#xa;2. Client creates a Prompt via POST /api/prompts on prompt-service; it is persisted in SQLite (prompt_manager.db) and returns an auto-generated UUID id.&#xa;3. Client submits a Review (POST /api/reviews) to prompt-review-service, including the promptId, reviewerName, score (1-5), and feedback.&#xa;4. ReviewController delegates to ReviewService, which uses PromptServiceClient (RestTemplate) to call GET /api/prompts/{id} on prompt-service to validate the prompt exists.&#xa;5. If the prompt exists (200 OK), review-service captures a promptSnapshot (copy of the prompt&#39;s content at review time), assigns an id and reviewedAt timestamp, and persists the Review as a JSON file via ReviewFileRepository (/reviews/ directory).&#xa;6. If prompt-service is unreachable, the review creation fails with 503. If the promptId does not exist, a 404 is returned instead of a review being created.&#xa;7. Clients can then query reviews (all, by promptId, by review id) or fetch an aggregated summary (GET /api/reviews/{promptId}/summary) with totalReviews, averageScore, and feedback list." vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="165" width="1260" x="120" y="517.5" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
      </root>
    </mxGraphModel>
  </diagram>
</mxfile>
